parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially at night, due to poor visibility.
symptoms: Headlights are extremely dim
making it difficult to see the roadway
especially at night; headlights stop working suddenly; low-beam and high-beam headlights become inoperable; reverse lights are not working
affecting the rear camera.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tail light can cause accidents or reduce visibility, especially at night.
symptoms: Bad tail light on one side; whole tail light needs to be replaced due to bad wiring; interior light flashes when stepping on the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of power steering can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Power steering assist temporarily goes out
especially during low-speed turning maneuvers
resulting in stiff or difficult steering. Warning lights
such as "Stabilitrak" and "Power Steering Assist - Drive with Care
" may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of power, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may shut off suddenly
resulting in loss of power steering
brakes
and other essential systems. Warning lights
such as "Service Stabilitrack
" may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and rack can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The steering column may become loose or faulty
causing the steering wheel to jerk or become difficult to turn. The steering rack may fail
resulting in partial or complete loss of steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Hard brake pedal
brake pedal becomes stiff
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop
vehicle takes longer to stop
brake system warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vacuum pump can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Brake pedal becomes firm
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop
vehicle takes longer to stop
brake system warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic brake control module can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Brake system warning lights illuminate
brake pedal becomes stiff
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop
vehicle takes longer to stop.
